<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>No Rules: The James Small Story - Reader Survey</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Segoe UI,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,Apple Color Emoji,Segoe UI Emoji;
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: #24292e;
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 20px;
        }
        h1 {
            border-bottom: 1px solid #eaecef;
            padding-bottom: 0.3em;
        }
        form {
            background: #f6f8fa;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 6px;
            border: 1px solid #e1e4e8;
        }
        label {
            display: block;
            margin-top: 15px;
            font-weight: 600;
        }
        input[type="text"], select, textarea {
            width: 100%;
            padding: 8px;
            margin-top: 5px;
            border: 1px solid #e1e4e8;
            border-radius: 6px;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }
        input[type="submit"] {
            background-color: #2ea44f;
            color: white;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 6px;
            cursor: pointer;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
        input[type="submit"]:hover {
            background-color: #2c974b;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>No Rules: The James Small Story - Reader Survey</h1>
    <form id="james-small-survey">
        <label for="name">1. What is your name:</label>
        <input type="text" id="name" name="name" required>

        <label for="most-compelling-section">2. Which section of the book did you find most compelling?</label>
        <select id="most-compelling-section" name="most-compelling-section" required>
            <option value="">Select an option</option>
            <option value="The Son">The Son</option>
            <option value="The Brother">The Brother</option>
            <option value="The Father">The Father</option>
            <option value="The Man">The Man</option>
            <option value="The Player">The Player</option>
            <option value="The Coach">The Coach</option>
            <option value="The Hero">The Hero</option>
            <option value="The Legend">The Legend</option>
            <option value="The Last Word">The Last Word</option>
        </select>

        <label for="perspective-balance">3. How well do you think the book balances different perspectives on James Small's life?</label>
        <select id="perspective-balance" name="perspective-balance" required>
            <option value="">Select an option</option>
            <option value="Excellent balance">Excellent balance</option>
            <option value="Very good balance">Very good balance</option>
            <option value="Good balance">Good balance</option>
            <option value="Fair balance">Fair balance</option>
            <option value="Poor balance">Poor balance</option>
        </select>

        <label for="photo-quality">4. How would you rate the quality and selection of photos in the book?</label>
        <select id="photo-quality" name="photo-quality" required>
            <option value="">Select an option</option>
            <option value="Excellent">Excellent</option>
            <option value="Very good">Very good</option>
            <option value="Good">Good</option>
            <option value="Fair">Fair</option>
            <option value="Poor">Poor</option>
        </select>

        <label for="new-insight">5. How much new insight did you gain into James Small's life and career?</label>
        <select id="new-insight" name="new-insight" required>
            <option value="">Select an option</option>
            <option value="A great deal">A great deal</option>
            <option value="Quite a bit">Quite a bit</option>
            <option value="A moderate amount">A moderate amount</option>
            <option value="A little">A little</option>
            <option value="None at all">None at all</option>
        </select>

        <label for="capture-of-james-small">6. How well do you think the book captures James Small as both a player and a person?</label>
        <select id="capture-of-james-small" name="capture-of-james-small" required>
            <option value="">Select an option</option>
            <option value="Extremely well">Extremely well</option>
            <option value="Very well">Very well</option>
            <option value="Well">Well</option>
            <option value="Somewhat well">Somewhat well</option>
            <option value="Not well at all">Not well at all</option>
        </select>

        <label for="emotional-impact">7. Which aspect of James Small's story had the most emotional impact on you?</label>
        <select id="emotional-impact" name="emotional-impact" required>
            <option value="">Select an option</option>
            <option value="His family relationships">His family relationships</option>
            <option value="His rugby career">His rugby career</option>
            <option value="His personal struggles">His personal struggles</option>
            <option value="His coaching career">His coaching career</option>
            <option value="His lasting legacy">His lasting legacy</option>
        </select>

        <label for="writing-quality">8. How would you rate the quality of writing by Gavin Rich and Simon Borchardt?</label>
        <select id="writing-quality" name="writing-quality" required>
            <option value="">Select an option</option>
            <option value="Excellent">Excellent</option>
            <option value="Very good">Very good</option>
            <option value="Good">Good</option>
            <option value="Fair">Fair</option>
            <option value="Poor">Poor</option>
        </select>

        <label for="book-format-satisfaction">9. How satisfied are you with the hardcover coffee-table book format?</label>
        <select id="book-format-satisfaction" name="book-format-satisfaction" required>
            <option value="">Select an option</option>
            <option value="Extremely satisfied">Extremely satisfied</option>
            <option value="Very satisfied">Very satisfied</option>
            <option value="Satisfied">Satisfied</option>
            <option value="Somewhat dissatisfied">Somewhat dissatisfied</option>
            <option value="Very dissatisfied">Very dissatisfied</option>
        </select>

        <label for="overall-rating">10. Overall, how would you rate "No Rules: The James Small Story"? (1-10)</label>
        <input type="range" id="overall-rating" name="overall-rating" min="1" max="10" value="5" required>
        <output for="overall-rating"></output>

        <label for="recommendation-likelihood">11. How likely are you to recommend this book to other rugby fans or those interested in South African sports history?</label>
        <select id="recommendation-likelihood" name="recommendation-likelihood" required>
            <option value="">Select an option</option>
            <option value="Extremely likely">Extremely likely</option>
            <option value="Very likely">Very likely</option>
            <option value="Somewhat likely">Somewhat likely</option>
            <option value="Not very likely">Not very likely</option>
            <option value="Not at all likely">Not at all likely</option>
        </select>

        <label for="additional-comments">12. Do you have any additional comments or feedback about the book?</label>
        <textarea id="additional-comments" name="additional-comments" rows="4"></textarea>

        <input type="submit" value="Submit Survey">
    </form>

    <script>
        document.getElementById('overall-rating').addEventListener('input', function(e) {
            e.target.nextElementSibling.value = e.target.value;
        });

        document.getElementById('james-small-survey').addEventListener('submit', function(e) {
            e.preventDefault();
            var formData = new FormData(e.target);
            var output = '';
            for (var pair of formData.entries()) {
                output += pair[0] + ': ' + pair[1] + '\n';
            }
            alert('Thank you for submitting the survey! Here are your responses:\n\n' + output);
            // In a real scenario, you'd send this data to a server
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
